Definition
<def>A primitive word;<lb/> <hi rend="italic">father</hi> in a literal and {immediate} or figurative and remote <hi rend="italic">application:</hi> - {chief} (fore-) father ({[-less]}) X {patrimony} principal. Compare names in "Abi-"</def> 
<def>(Chaldee); corresponding to <ref target="StrongsHebrew:1">H1</ref>: - father.</def> 
<def>From the same as <ref target="StrongsHebrew:24">H24</ref>; a <hi rend="italic">green</hi> <hi rend="italic">plant:</hi> - {greenness} fruit.</def> 
<def>(Chaldee); corresponding to <ref target="StrongsHebrew:3">H3</ref>: - fruit.</def> 
<def>Of foreign origin;<lb/> <hi rend="italic">{Abagtha}</hi> a eunuch of <hi rend="italic">Xerxes:</hi> - Abagtha.</def> 
<def>A primitive root; properly to <hi rend="italic">wander</hi> {away} that is <hi rend="italic">lose</hi> oneself; by implication to <hi rend="italic">perish</hi> ({causatively} <hi rend="italic">destroy</hi>): - {break} destroy ({-uction}) + not {escape} {fail} {lose} (cause {to} make) {perish} {spend} X and {surely} {take} be {undone} X {utterly} be void {of} have no way to flee.</def> 
<def>(Chaldee); corresponding to <ref target="StrongsHebrew:6">H6</ref>: - {destroy} perish.</def> 
<def>Active participle of <ref target="StrongsHebrew:6">H6</ref>; (concretely) <hi rend="italic">wretched</hi> or (abstractly) <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">destruction:</hi></hi> - perish.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:6">H6</ref>; concretely something <hi rend="italic">lost</hi>; abstractly <hi rend="italic">{destruction}</hi> that is <hi rend="italic">Hades:</hi> - lost. Compare <ref target="StrongsHebrew:10">H10</ref>.</def> 
<def>The same as {<ref target="StrongsHebrew:9">H9</ref>} miswritten for <ref target="StrongsHebrew:11">H11</ref>; a <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">perishing:</hi></hi> - destruction.</def> 
<def>Intensively from <ref target="StrongsHebrew:6">H6</ref>; abstractly a <hi rend="italic">perishing</hi>; concretely <hi rend="italic">Hades:</hi> - destruction.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:6">H6</ref>; a <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">perishing:</hi></hi> - destruction.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:6">H6</ref>; a <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">perishing:</hi></hi> - destruction.</def> 
<def>A primitive root; to <hi rend="italic">breathe</hi> {after} that is (figuratively) to <hi rend="italic">be</hi> <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">acquiescent:</hi></hi> - {consent} rest {content} {will} be willing.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:14">H14</ref>; <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">longing:</hi></hi> - desire.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:14">H14</ref> (in the sense of <hi rend="italic">bending</hi> towards); the <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">papyrus:</hi></hi> - swift.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:14">H14</ref> (in the sense of <hi rend="italic">desiring</hi>); <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">want:</hi></hi> - sorrow.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:75">H75</ref>; a <hi rend="italic">manger</hi> or <hi rend="italic"><hi rend="italic">stall:</hi></hi> - crib.</def> 
<def>From an unused root (apparently meaning to <hi rend="italic">turn</hi>);<lb/> <hi rend="italic">brandishing</hi> of a <hi rend="italic">sword:</hi> - point.</def> 
<def>Of uncertain derivation; a <hi rend="italic">melon</hi> (only plural): - melon.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:1">H1</ref>; <hi rend="italic">fatherly</hi>;<lb/> <hi rend="italic">{Abi}</hi> Hezekiah´ s <hi rend="italic">mother:</hi> - Abi.</def> 
<def>From <ref target="StrongsHebrew:1">H1</ref> and <ref target="StrongsHebrew:410">H410</ref>; <hi rend="italic">father</hi> (that is <hi rend="italic">possessor</hi>) <hi rend="italic">of God</hi>;<lb/> <hi rend="italic">{Abiel}</hi> the name of two <hi rend="italic">Israelites:</hi> - Abiel.</def>
